U.S. and S. Korean Warmongers' Projected War Exercises Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 18 (KCNA) -- The south Korea-U.S. Combined Forces Command officially announced that it would stage Ulji Freedom Guardian, the first puppet army-led south Korea-U.S. joint military exercises, from August 18 to 22 with at least 10,000 U.S. forces stationed abroad and in south Korea involved. A spokesman for the Korean National Peace Committee issued a statement Friday denouncing the projected saber-rattling.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Branding the joint exercises as DPRK-targeted provocative war exercises that replaced the Ulji Focus Lens which the U.S. and the puppet warmongers staged on an annual basis from mid-1970s, the statement continued:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is an open declaration of confrontation with the DPRK and an outright challenge to the Koreans and the international community desirous of peace and stability on the Korean Peninsula.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The projected U.S. and the south Korean warmongers' saber-rattling would only escalate tension and the danger of a nuclear war on the Korean Peninsula and gravely threaten stability in Northeast Asia.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The warmongers of the U.S. and the south Korean puppet forces are trying hard to justify the war exercises, claiming that they are aimed at "defense." But with nothing can they cover up their aggressive nature.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality goes to clearly prove that the "dialogue", "peace" and "improved relations" touted by the U.S. and the Lee Myung Bak group are nothing but an empty talk and they only seek confrontation and war.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will never tolerate the provocateurs' moves for a war of aggression against the north, the moves aimed to tarnish the dignity and sovereignty of the Korean nation, but will resolutely counter them with a powerful measure for self-defence.

KCNA Rebukes Japan's Moves for Reinvasion 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 18 (KCNA) -- The Japanese Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology on July 14 distributed to middle schools across the country "new teaching guidelines" calling for educating students in the important role the "Self-Defense Forces" (SDF)  has to play for the "defence of Japan and maintenance of peace and security in the international community".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This prompted the Japanese middle schools to put the main emphasis of education concerning the SDF on its "international activities", not on the process of its building as in the past.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This proves that the criminal moves of the descendents of Samurais to stoke the militarist zeal for overseas expansion among the rising generation and thus lay an ideological and moral groundwork for launching reinvasion have reached a more dangerous phase.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The SDF is in the process of turning into forces for preemptive attacks after completely discarding the cumbersome signboard of "exclusive defence."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "international activities" of the SDF are nothing but open war actions to make overseas military operations and intervention an established fact and get proficient in their methods.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To paint this as one for "a peaceful purpose" and impart this into the minds of the rising generation of Japan is aimed to imbue them with extreme arrogance and militarist idea from their childhood and thus train them as a shock brigade for aggression.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries' moves to let the militarist idea run through the spiritual education of the rising generation in a bid to build an ideological and moral groundwork for reinvasion have started long ago.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The goal of "educational reform" openly pushed forward by the Japanese authorities in the new century is to modify the 1946 "fundamental law of education" which was instituted to ban education in "imperialist Japan" and include in it a "royal order" concerning education instituted by "emperor" in 1896 and thus revive the militarist view on history and ultra-nationalism.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is in the course of such reactionary "educational reform" that the national flag and the national anthem dating back to the era of "empire" have been revived and young Japanese are taught distorted history and misguided self-confidence and totalitarian and chauvinistic view on life. This reality of Japan reminds one of the dark era when Japan waged the "national spiritual general mobilization movement" under the slogans of "Let's go to Manchuria!" and "Let's go to Pacific!"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the ultra-right forces that are taking the lead in stirring up this social atmosphere. They do not hesitate to utter bellicose remarks that "Japan will meet ruin if the prime minister stops visiting 'Yasukuni Shrine'" and "even 'small-scale war' with China should be considered," etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's preparations for war have, in fact, reached a final phase given that it is pushing forward the replacement of the "pacifist constitution" by a war constitution and the reorganization of the SDF into "armed forces for self-defense" following the institution of various laws for the execution of war.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The international community is growing vigilant against the Japanese ultra-right forces' stepped-up ideological and moral preparations in step with the legal and military ones for reinvasion while openly calling for building "Japan capable of fighting a war".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries had better stop running amuck, pondering over the serious consequences to be entailed by their reckless moves for reinvasion.

Lee Myung Bak Group Bound to Go to Ruin 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 18 (KCNA) -- The Lee Myung Bak group is making desperate efforts to calm down the candlelight protesters and tide over its ruling crisis through double-dealing tactics-- appeasement and deception and fascist crackdown--but the Lee treacherous regime is bound to go to ruin as it is forsaken by the people.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed article.
 It goes on:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The vigorous massive candlelight actions now underway in south Korea are an inevitable product of the Lee group's sycophantic, treacherous and unpopular policy.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sycophantic and treacherous politics pursued by traitor Lee is censured for being the most disgraceful, humiliating and treacherous politics in history.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He is vociferous about "economic recovery" but rendering the economy and people's living more bankrupt.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee group has not taken any measure to save economy from bankruptcy. Yet, it is working with bloodshot eyes to stem the trend of the June 15 era of reunification and foster the inter-Korean confrontation, stepping up its policy of confrontation with the DPRK as regards the inter-Korean relations issue. His anti-reunification confrontational policy resulted in freezing the relations between the north and the south which had favorably developed since the publication of the June 15 joint declaration and putting the inter-Korean cooperation undertakings on the verge of breakdown.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The hatred and resentment of the south Koreans at Lee triggered off massive candlelight demonstrations.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sycophants and traitors are bound to meet self-destruction as they rule over the people and infringe upon the dignity and interests of the nation, backed by foreign forces. This is the truth taught by history.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Suppression is by no means a cure-all. No brutal crackdown can arrest the struggle of the people. The days of the fascist tyrant are numbered.

Full Display of Mental Power Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 18 (KCNA) -- The present general advance is that based on ideology, and a great revolutionary offensive should be launched on the ideological front to give full play to the inexhaustible mental power of the army and the people.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun says this in a signed article on Friday.
 The present general advance is mainly characterized by the advance of ideology that makes it possible to bring about historic turn in building a prosperous and powerful nation by giving vent to the great mental power of the army and people like the erupting volcano. That is why it has inexhaustible might, the article notes, and goes on:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the revolutionary advance fully demonstrating the might of our single-minded unity in which the army and people are closely rallied around the headquarters of revolution with the same idea and purpose.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the greatest pride of our party and revolution that the harmonious whole of the leader and the people and the spirit of the great unity have been creditably carried forward to prevail in the whole society century after century.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ongoing general advance is the march of creation and change in which the Korean people would overcome any sorts of difficulties and hardships and make a leap forward with the might of their strong and independent faith and revolutionary spirit of self-reliance.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of revolutionary great upsurge in socialist Korea will be given steady continuity as its army and people's hearts are beating high with the revolutionary spirit of self-reliance created in the thick forests of Mt. Paektu.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is also an all-people advance for firmly defending our ideology, system and socialist way of life with the revolutionary ideological offensive.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There can be no change in the revolutionary principle and stand of our army and people to resolutely smash the imperialists' reactionary ideological and cultural poisoning with the said offensive. Our ideological position is stable and our own style socialism impregnable as there are the revolutionary army and people who do not make the any slightest compromise or concession in the showdown with imperialism.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present general advance will be registered in the nation's history as a historic advance bringing about the era of enormous creation and change while fully displaying the inexhaustible mental power of Songun Korea as it is led by Kim Jong Il, a prominent thinker and theoretician and a great statesman.

"Forced March in Mid-summer" Recorded in Songun History 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 18 (KCNA) -- The Songun history of the DPRK has recorded many legends of the great man which touch the heart-strings of all people.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Among them is the legend of "forced march in mid-summer" telling of the ardent patriotic devotion of leader Kim Jong Il.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He who regards the troubles for the country and people as pleasure gave historic on-the-spot guidance to east coastal district last summer when it was hottest in scores of years, coupled with downpours which triggered off a heavy flood instantly.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The units to which he gave on-the-spot guidance reported in August numbered nearly 20.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The on-the-spot guidance he gave, covering scores of kilometers, even hundreds of kilometers, a day was beyond human imagination.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He made the long trip of patriotic devotion, defying the unfavorable weather conditions, to bring earlier the morrow of a rich and powerful country where the people would enjoy happiness. The Korean people call it "forced march in mid-summer," recollecting it with deep emotion.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
This summer, too, he continues his field guidance to units of the Korean People's Army and various sectors of the national economy.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He visited Jagang Province when the whole country was full of boundless yearning and reverence for President Kim Il Sung. The photographs of leader Kim Jong Il looking round the statue of President Kim Il Sung erected in Hwaphyong County and historical Kanggye Post Office revolutionary site hardened the Korean people's will to accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche through generations.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
While visiting the Unhung Cooperative Farm in Thaechon County, he highly appreciated the success achieved by the officials and working people of the farm and showed deep trust in them, saying that they should set an example in agricultural production to be followed by the whole country.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
At the Phyongbuk Pig Farm and Thaechon Youth Rabbit Breed Farm, he put forth tasks and ways to improve the dietary life of the people and acquainted himself with the afforestation underway in North Phyongan Province.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He, calling at People's Army units, looked after the living conditions as a whole from TV view and temperature and humidity of bedrooms to storage of subsidiary food and quality of water of wash cum bath rooms with paternal love, thus giving matchless courage to them.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He continues the "forced march in mid-summer" for the future of the rich and powerful country today when the beauty spots and bathing resorts throughout the country are reverberating with happy laughter of the people. His inspection tour will bring earlier the day of victory in the building of a great, prosperous and powerful nation.

Friendly Meeting Held with Mongolians 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 18 (KCNA) -- A friendly meeting was held at DPRK-Mongolia Friendship Pyongyang Songyo Middle School No. 1 today on the occasion of the 20th anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's visit to Mongolia.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Ambassador Sodovjamts Khurelbaatar and staff members of the Mongolian embassy here and members of the visiting friendly delegation of the "Neajin International" Trade Co., Ltd. of Mongolia.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pak Kyong Il, vice-chairman of the DPRK-Mongolia Friendship Association, and others were on hand.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to the meeting, the guests went round educational facilities at the school and donated to it the educational equipment prepared by them.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the meeting talked with each other about the matter of further developing the cooperative relations between the two countries, deepening friendship.

Commemorative Stamp of 29th Olympic Torch Relay Published 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 18 (KCNA) -- A new postage stamp (souvenir sheet) has been released in commemoration of the 29th Olympic torch relay held in Pyongyang in April.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Printed on the top of the sheet are the words "29th Olympic Torch Relay Pyongyang April 28, Juche 97 (2008)", under which there is a stamp showing a poster on the theme of "Light the Passion, Share the Dream."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On both sides of the stamp there are the Tower of the Juche Idea and Kim Il Sung Stadium against the background of Pyongyang citizens cheering the torch relay with bouquets in their hands.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Brought out in the meantime are stamps showing serpentine, chalcopyrite, zinc blende and molybdenite which are distributed in different parts of Korea.

Schoolchildren's Summer Camping Brisk in DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 18 (KCNA) -- Schoolchildren have pleasant summer camping at the children's camps located in scenic spots in different parts of the DPRK.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The camps were successfully renovated to be centers for extracurricular education under the loving care of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il. They are equipped with all amenities and different kinds of sports and entertainment facilities to enable the children to enjoy their camping.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The camps have drawn at least 4.7 million schoolchildren for the last decades.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Camping started at those camps this year, too, on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The children's camps in Mts. Myohyang and Ryongak and Songdowon, Lake Yonphung and in other places are now animated with campers.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The schoolchildren spending their joyful days at the Mangyongdae Children's Camp visited such revolutionary sites as the old home of the President in Mangyongdae and the warship rock to deeply grasp his revolutionary history.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The schoolchildren are climbing Mt. Myohyang widely known for its spectacular scenery to command a bird's-eye view of the Manphok Valley and the Sangwon Hermitage and nurture patriotism.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Schoolchildren are making their camping days pleasant with maritime sporting activities and sports games and other programs at the Sokam and Sohungho children's camps on the shores of scenic lakes and the Soho and Kyongpho children's camps on the east coast.

Impeachment of Lee Myung Bak Urged in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 18 (KCNA) -- The Democratic Party of south Korea held on July 15 that traitor Lee Myung Bak should be impeached, according to south Korean CBS.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The party quoted the Japanese Yomiuri Shimbun saying: When Japanese Prime Minister Fukuda said Japan had no option but to make a reference to Takeshima in the "explanation about the new guidelines for schools" as regards the social subjects of primary and middle schools during Lee Myung Bak's recent trip to Japan, Lee responded to him by uttering "Please wait."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The party stated: "If it is true that the president said so when hearing such absurd remark from Fukuda though he is obliged to defend the territory of his country, it was obviously a violation of the Constitution". He deserves an impeachment from a legal point of view.

Japan's Moves to Grab Tok Islet Protested in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 18 (KCNA) -- The struggle against Japan's moves to grab Tok Islet was waged across south Korea on July 15.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Civic and public organizations respectively held press conferences outside the Japanese embassy in Seoul.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 39 civic and public organizations including the Solidarity for Progress of south Korea said that Japan's persistent "claim to Tok Islet" is aimed at gratifying its ambition for reinvasion of the Korean Peninsula and greed and that it will be the only and wise choice for the Japanese government to abandon its "claim to the islet."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organizations called upon all the people to turn out in the struggle not to tolerate any aggression and provocation of Japan but to defend Tok Islet.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that Japan's ceaseless scheme to grab Tok Islet is ascribable to the humiliating diplomacy of the south Korean "government", they urged the Lee Myung Bak "government" to take a positive and tough counteraction over the issue of Tok Islet.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants staged a protest demonstration, chanting such slogans as "The Japanese government should apologize for the attempted aggression of Tok Islet and distortion of history!" and "The Lee Myung Bak 'government' incompetent and disgraceful in diplomacy should resign!"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Teachers' Union (Jongyojo), the south Korean General Federation of Teachers' Organizations strongly condemned Japan's description of its "dominium over Tok Islet" as an act of distorting history and invading the islet.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then, they handed a letter of protest to the Japanese embassy.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Teachers affiliated to the Kwangju and South Jolla Provincial Branch of Jongyojo, the Kwangju General Federation of Civic Organizations and the Education Office in Chongju City, North Chungchong Province joined the struggle to denounce Japan's brazen-faced moves to grab Tok Islet.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Posted on Internet homepages of south Korea were a large number of articles slashing at the above-said moves.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the Press Headquarters of the South Side Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration and the Group for Defending Tok Islet issued statements on July 14 protesting the moves.

Great Career of Kim Il Sung Highly Praised
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 18 (KCNA) -- Round-table talks, reading sessions and film shows were held in Russia, Ukraine, Brazil and Democratic Congo between July 2 and 9 to commemorate the 14th anniversary of demise of President Kim Il Sung.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants of the film shows watched Korean films dealing with the revolutionary history and undying exploits of the President.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Gennadi Sharin, a composer of Russia, said at a film show that the President is the peerlessly great man who has been deeply revered by the world progressive people.
 The president of a Ukrainian company said that through the film show he came to know better about the noble virtue of Kim Il Sung, who took good care of the anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters, and the noble mental world of the fighters, who defended him at the cost of their lives.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Brasilia City Committee of the Brazilian Communist Party said at the round-table talks that Kim Il Sung is a distinguished leader recognized by the whole world and that he has enjoyed boundless reverence of all people for his enormous feats for the country and the nation and humankind.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vele Mukelenge, chairman of the Group for the Study of the Juche Idea of the University of Kinshasa in Democratic Congo, said at a reading session on Kim Il Sung's reminiscences "With the Century": The undying exploits performed by the President, who put forward the Songun idea and defeated with arms the heinous Japanese imperialists armed to the teeth, will remain long in the history of the anti-imperialist national liberation struggle.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the Songun policy pursued by leader Kim Jong Il, the DPRK has become the mental pillar for the progressive people and the Juche idea followers the world over, the chairman stated.

Kim Il Sung's Work Published in Venezuela
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 18 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il Sung's famous work "Let Us Shatter Imperialist Moves towards Aggression and War and Safeguard Peace and Independence" was brought out in booklet by the Canta Clara Publishing House of Venezuela on July 7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, published on July 3, Juche 72 (1983), underlines the significance of the world conference of journalists and clarifies the idea that to oppose aggression and war and safeguard peace and independence is the most urgent task facing the world progressive people.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also expounded in it are the noble mission and role of the world progressive media persons and the idea that it is the consistent foreign policy of the DPRK government to stand for peace and independence against imperialism and strengthen friendship and solidarity with peoples of different countries.

Kim Jong Il presencia funcion de conjunto de danza "Beriozka"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 18 de julio (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea y Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea presencio la funcion del Conjunto de Danza Academica Nacional "Beriozka" N. S. Nadezhdina de Rusia, de visita en Corea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
En el teatro el Dirigente fue acogido por Mira Koltsova, jefa del conjunto de danza y Alexander Matsegora, encargado de negocios a.i. de la Federacion  Rusa en Corea
El expreso agradecimiento a los artistas rusos quienes estimularon a traves de su entusiasta funcion la lucha del pueblo coreano por acoger con brillantes exitos laborales el 60o aniversario de la fundacion de la RPDC y departio cordialmente con los huespedes.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
El conjunto de danza de larga historia y tradicion puso en la escena iniciada con el coro de "Cancion del General Kim Jong Il" la danza femenina en grupo "Beriozka", la masculina en grupo "Bromistas" y las mixtas en grupo "En memoria de los defensores de la patria" y "Vasta llanura", el baile comico "Solterones", el solo de baile "Recuerdo", la suite coreografica "Suceso de hace mucho tiempo", las canciones y bailes "Beriozka", "Noche en el suburbio de Moscu", "Katyusha" y "Laguna de flores" de la opera revolucionaria coreana "!Cuentalo, bosque!" y otras piezas.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Los ejecutantes mostraron bien con habilidad artistica y elegantes ritmos el ferviente amor a la patria, la vida optimista y laboriosa y costumbres nacionales del pueblo ruso.
La funcion concluyo con el coro de la cancion coreana "General de Corea".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
El Dirigente felicito a los artistas rusos por su exito en la funcion  y les envio su saludo.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
La jefa del Conjunto de Danza rindio el mas cordial agradecimiento al Dirigente Kim Jong Il por haber visto en persona la funcion y prestado profunda atencion a sus actividades de creacion artistica recogiendo el unanime sentimiento de veneracion de todos los artistas rusos hacia el.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Estuvieron presentes el secretario del CC del PTC Choe Thae Bok, el primer vicecanciller Kang Sok Ju, los generales de ejercito Hyon Chol Hae y Ri Myong Su, oficiales y soldados, del Ejercito Popular de Corea, los creadores y artistas del ejercito y la sociedad.

ATCC comenta nueva campana de movilizacion espiritual en Japon
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 18 de julio (ATCC) -- El Ministerio de Educacion, Cultura, Deportes, Ciencia y Tecnologia de Japon hizo publica el dia 14 la nueva "Guia de ensenanza", que exige a las escuelas secundarias de todo el pais impartir la educacion en el papel de las "Fuerzas de Autodefensa" para la "defensa de Japon y el mantenimiento de la paz y seguridad de la sociedad internacional".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Segun ella, las escuelas secundarias de Japon daran enfasis de la ensenanza sobre las "Fuerzas de Autodefensa" no en el proceso de su fundacion sino en sus "actividades en la arena internacional".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Esto demuestra que entraron en la etapa mas peligrosa las maniobras criminales de los descendientes de los samurais encaminadas a sentar la  base ideo-espiritual para la nueva agresion al sembrar el entusiasmo por el expansionismo militarista a ultramar entre las nuevas generaciones.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Las "Fuerzas de Autodefensa" de Japon se convierten en las tropas para el ataque preventivo sin comprometerse en nada a su molesta mision de "defensa exclusiva".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 En particular, sus "actividades internacionales" no son mas que abiertas maniobras belicas para ejercitar los metodos de operaciones e intervencion militares en ultramar considerandolas como hechos consumados.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pero, las autoridades japonesas tratan de ensenar esas actividades a las nuevas generaciones distorsionandolas como "pacifistas" partiendo de su objetivo de formar a los japoneses como vanguardias de agresion inyectados desde nino de extrema arrogancia y de idea militarista.
 Comenzaron mucho antes las tentativas de los reaccionarios japoneses de establecer el marco ideo-espiritual de la nueva agresion impartiendo a las nuevas generaciones la educacion espiritual fundamentada en la idea militarista.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 La meta de la "reforma educacional", que las autoridades japonesas impulsan de manera mas abierta en el nuevo siglo, es reproducir la concepcion de la historia militarista y el ultranacionalismo al enmendar la "ley principal de educacion" instituida en 1946 para prohibir la educacion de "Japon imperialista" y al estipular en ella el "decreto de educacion" elaborado en 1896 por el "emperador".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 En el proceso de la reaccionaria "reforma educacional" se rehabilitaron ya la bandera nacional y el himno nacional de la epoca "imperial" y se inculcan en las nuevas generaciones la historia tergiversada, el orgullo malsano y el punto de vista de la vida totalitario y chovinista.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Esta realidad de Japon hace recordar aquella epoca obscurantista cuando los japoneses libraban la "campana de movilizacion espiritual general del pueblo" gritando las consignas "!Vamos a Manchuria!" y "!Vamos al Pacifico!"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Las fuerzas ultraderechistas, que encauzan tal ambiente social, no vacilan en pronunciar palabras belicosas como "Japon se arruinara si el premier deja de visitar el 'santuario de Yasukuni'" y "Es preciso examinar hasta la guerra de 'pequeno tamano' con China".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japon instituyo las leyes por ramas para la guerra e impulsa la enmienda de la "Constitucion pacifista" como la de guerra y la reorganizacion de las "Fuerzas de Autodefensa" como "ejercito autodefensivo".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Efectivamente, los preparativos belicos de Japon estan en etapa de acabado.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 La sociedad internacional esta tomando precaucion de que las fuerzas ultraderechistas de Japon impulsan activamente los preparativos ideo-espirituales al paralelo de los juridicos y militares para la nueva agresion preconizando abiertamente la conversion de su pais en "Japon capaz de hacer la guerra".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Los reaccionarios japoneses deben actuar con prudencia tras reflexionar seriamente de las graves consecuencias que emanen de sus insensatas maniobras para la nueva agresion.
